

---
const pageTitle = "Shadow";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(245,245,245,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(-6deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.2;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #f3f3f3, #ebebeb);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0 14px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .content-layer p,
      .content-layer h1,
      .content-layer h2,
      .content-layer .subtitle,
      .content-layer .divider,
      .content-layer .quote,
      .content-layer .mini-links,
      .content-layer .footer-note {
        text-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        h1 { font-size: 34px; }
        .symbol-bg {
          width: 210px;
          height: 210px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">archetypes index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/archetypes/hero">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/archetypes/anima">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="86" />
              <path d="M190 78
                       C150 98, 132 136, 136 170
                       C140 208, 168 236, 202 246
                       C170 250, 132 240, 106 214
                       C82 190, 70 154, 78 120
                       C88 92, 110 70, 138 58
                       C156 50, 176 48, 190 52" />
              <path d="M92 100 L208 216" />
              <path d="M108 84 L224 200" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Shadow</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">archetypes / repression / unknown self / archive entry 002</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The shadow represents the parts of the self that are not accepted,
            not seen, or not consciously lived. It forms from what is rejected
            during development, whether for social, moral, or personal reasons.
          </p>

          <p>
            These elements do not disappear. They remain active beneath the surface,
            influencing behavior, emotion, and perception in indirect ways.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            what is denied does not vanish, it moves out of sight.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">repression and projection</h2>

          <p>
            The shadow often appears through projection. Traits that are difficult
            to accept in oneself are seen in others, sometimes exaggerated or
            emotionally charged.
          </p>

          <p>
            This is why strong reactions can point toward shadow material. What is
            most resisted outwardly may be connected to something inwardly unrecognized.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">integration</h2>

          <p>
            Working with the shadow is not about becoming it, but about recognizing
            its presence. When brought into awareness, shadow elements lose some of
            their compulsive force.
          </p>

          <p>
            Integration allows a broader range of experience without fragmentation.
            It increases depth, realism, and psychological balance.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">back to archetypes index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/anima">continue to: anima</a>
            <a class="red" href="/archetypes/hero">hero</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>